Performance overlays for the satosa and saml2 packages used by the SATOSA Skolverket proxy

Changes:
sigver.py - remove half the subproccess calls by hardcoding xmlsec1 version
state.py  - change lzma to zlib for cookie compression

These files patch installed Python packages in the SATOSA virtualenv:
sigver.py -> import package saml2 (distribution: pysaml2)
state.py  -> import package satosa

The SATOSA image now applies them through apply-package-overlays.sh, which:
- resolves the installed package path using /opt/eduid/satosa_scim/bin/python
- reads patches/manifest.txt to map import packages to overlay files
- fails the build if the expected package target file is missing
